modules.description: Provides functions to encode and decode JSON Web Tokens, including signing with a secret key and verifying signature integrity. Works with strings for tokens and associative arrays for payload data. Used to securely transmit user authentication claims between parties in a web application.

The module provides functions for parsing, serializing, and manipulating JSON Web Token (JWT) components, including extracting and adding claims like "ctyp," "alg," and "nonce," as well as converting between JSON representations and payload structures. It works with structured data types such as headers, claims, payloads, and tokens, enabling operations like algorithm conversion and component access. Use cases include validating token integrity, extracting specific claim values, and serializing data for secure transmission.
